prompt:
Add a new public function called Factorial to Calculator.calr. Since Calor doesn't support recursion or loops in expressions, implement a simplified version that handles small inputs using nested ternary. It takes i32 parameter n (with precondition 0 <= n <= 5) and returns i32. Use function ID f003.

Use this pattern:
§F{f003:Factorial:pub}
  §I{i32:n}
  §O{i32}
  §Q (>= n 0)
  §Q (<= n 5)
  §S (>= result 1)
  §R (? (<= n 1) 1 (? (== n 2) 2 (? (== n 3) 6 (? (== n 4) 24 120))))
§/F{f003}

This returns: 1 for n<=1, 2 for n=2, 6 for n=3, 24 for n=4, 120 for n=5.
